3. UPSTREAM SUBSTRATE SOURCE LICENSES
   ----------------------------------
   The substrate is derived from four databases, each governed by its
   own license. When using the substrate, you must comply with all four:

   - Reactome — CC-BY 4.0; https://reactome.org/license
   - StringDB — CC-BY 4.0; https://string-db.org/cgi/access?footer_active_subpage=licensing
   - HMDB     — Academic redistribution permitted with attribution;
                 see https://hmdb.ca/about for commercial inquiries
   - KEGG     — Academic redistribution permitted; commercial use
                 requires a license from Pathway Solutions Inc.

   We have included from each source only the structured ontological
   metadata (reactions, reactants, products, pathway memberships) needed
   to compose the substrate, not the underlying full database content.
